ted for creative concepts\n- **Cost:** Near-zero\n- **Example:** Generate before/after ranking chart (10 keywords ‚Üí 100 keywords) as visual proof\n\n**Tier 4: Human Handoff**\n- **When:** Client-specific brand assets, high-stakes campaign, complex design\n- **Canvas provides:** Design brief, dimensions, copy, brand specs, wireframe/mockup\n- **Human delivers:** Polished design (Photoshop, Illustrator, Figma)\n\n---\n\n## **Recommended Implementation Plan**\n\n### **Phase 1 (Build Now):**\n1. **Video Tier 1:** Screen recording + FFmpeg editing (for SaaS demos)\n2. **Static Tier 1:** DALL-E 3 integration (AI image generation with CRO prompts)\n3. **Static Tier 3:** Template-based charts/data viz (for proof-driven ads)\n4. **Quality Gate:** Razor reviews all Canvas output for CRO compliance before Blitz uses it\n\n### **Phase 2 (Add Later):**\n5. **Video Tier 2:** Stock footage + text overlay templates (FFmpeg)\n6. **Static Tier 2:** Canva browser automation (for brand-consistent templates)\n\n### **Phase 3 (If Budget Allows):**\n7. **Video Tier 3:** AI video generation API (Pictory or Synthesia)\n\n### **Always Available:**\n8. **Human Handoff Tiers:** Canvas generates specs, human designer executes, Canvas validates\n\n---\n\n## **CRO Principles Baked Into Canvas**\n\nWhen Canvas generates any ad creative, it follows these rules:\n\n**Visual Hierarchy:**\n- Primary message (headline) = top-third or center, largest text\n- CTA = bottom-right or center-bottom, high-contrast button\n- Brand logo = top-left or bottom-corner, small but visible\n\n**Contrast & Readability:**\n- Text overlays on images: add dark gradient overlay or solid background box\n- CTA button: contrasting color (not brand color if brand is low-contrast)\n- Font: Sans-serif, bold for headlines, medium for body\n\n**Benefit-Driven Messaging:**\n- Headline communicates outcome, not feature\n  - ‚úÖ \"Rank for 100+ Keywords in 90 Days\"\n  - ‚ùå \"Topical Map Software\"\n- Subheadline adds specificity or urgency\n  - ‚úÖ \"Limited Spots ‚Äî Book Free Consultation\"\n\n**Social Proof / Trust Signals (when applicable):**\n- Client count (\"Join 500+ Agencies\")\n- Star ratings (if reviews exist)\n- Recognizable brand logos (if client list exists)\n\n**Platform-Specific Specs:**\n- **Meta Feed:** 1080x1080 (square), 1200x628 (landscape)\n- **Meta Stories/Reels:** 1080x1920 (9:16 vertical)\n- **Google Display:** 300x250, 728x90, 160x600 (standard IAB sizes)\n- **TikTok:** 1080x1920 (9:16 vertical), 9-15s optimal length\n\n---\n\n## **Quality Gate: Razor Reviews Canvas Output**\n\n**Before Blitz uses any ad creative:**\n1. Canvas generates creative (image or video)\n2. Canvas ‚Üí Razor: \"CRO review this ad creative\"\n3. Razor checks:\n   - Is value prop clear?\n   - Is CTA visible and action-oriented?\n   - Does visual hierarchy guide eye to CTA?\n   - Is contrast sufficient (text readable)?\n   - Does it match platform specs?\n4. Razor ‚Üí Canvas: \"Approved\" or \"Revise: [specific issues]\"\n5. Canvas revises if needed\n6. Canvas ‚Üí Blitz: \"Creative ready for campaign\"\n\n**This ensures every ad creative is CRO-optimized before it goes live.**\n\n---\n\n## **Cost Estimate (Monthly, for ~10 Campaigns)**\n\n**Conservative (Tier 1 Only):**\n- DALL-E 3: ~$5-10/month (50-100 images @ $0.04-0.08 each)\n- Screen recording + FFmpeg: $0 (just compute)\n- **Total: ~$10/month**\n\n**Mid-Range (Tier 1 + Tier 2):**\n- DALL-E 3: $10/month\n- Canva Pro: $13/month\n- Stock footage + FFmpeg: $0\n- **Total: ~$25/month**\n\n**Full Stack (All Tiers):**\n- DALL-E 3: $10/month\n- Canva Pro: $13/month\n- Pictory or Synthesia: $30-50/month\n- **Total: ~$55-75/month**\n\n**ROI:** If one campaign generates 10 leads @ $50 CPA = $500 value, the $55/month tooling cost is negligible.\n\n---\n\n## **My Recommendation**\n\n**Start with Phase 1:**\n- DALL-E 3 for static images (fast, high-quality, CRO-promptable)\n- Screen recording + FFmpeg for video demos (authentic, fast, free)\n- Template